<paragraph blockId="372.[151,1436,978,1364]" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[269,525,1158,1185]" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" refId="ref368338" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 226 pp. + [2] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1856">Rondani’s (1856: 113)</bibRefCitation>
key for the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1856" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[747,1046,1158,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Spathulina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,868,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Spathulina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[878,1046,1158,1185]" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" refId="ref368338" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 226 pp. + [2] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1856">Rondani, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
lists 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1309,1158,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Spathulina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sicula">
<emphasis box="[1111,1309,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Spathulina sicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its type species, but he did not provide a detailed description, type locality, 
<taxonomicName box="[984,1070,1194,1220]" family="Number" pageId="372" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or sex of the specimens. In his redescription 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[354,601,1230,1257]" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" pagination="161 - 188" refId="ref370303" refString="Rondani, C. (1871 c) Ortalidinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterologiae italicae prodromi. Pars VII - Fasc. 1. [concl.]. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 3 (2), 161 - 188." type="journal article" year="1871">Rondani (1871c: 168)</bibRefCitation>
specified having a single female: “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">
Foeminam unicam in 
<collectingRegion box="[1252,1324,1230,1256]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Sicilia</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName box="[1332,1414,1231,1256]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Etruria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="372" pageNumber="373" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="captam">captam</taxonomicName>
a Ghiliani, olim Clar. Spinola mihi transmisit
</emphasis>
[Mr. Spinola formerly sent to me a single female collected in 
<collectingRegion country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">Sicilia</collectingRegion>
by Ghiliani]”. We consider the single MZUF female as the 
<typeStatus box="[918,1016,1302,1328]" pageId="372" pageNumber="373">holotype</typeStatus>
(I.C.Z.N. 1999: Articles 72.4.1.1 and 73.1.2).
</paragraph>
